# generatedContent

**Instance Property**

This instance represented as generated content.

## Declaration

```swift
var generatedContent: GeneratedContent { get }
```

## Discussion

Conformance to this protocol is provided by the `@Generable` macro. A manual implementation may be used to map values onto properties using different names. Use the generated content property as shown below, to manually return a new [doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/GeneratedContent] with the properties you specify.

```swift
struct Person: ConvertibleToGeneratedContent {
   var name: String
   var age: Int

   var generatedContent: GeneratedContent {
       GeneratedContent(properties: [
           "firstName": name,
           "ageInYears": age
       ])
   }
}
```
